Moko bacteria disease was first confirmed in South Grenada in 1978 it spread northward even to Carricou. Quick action by Gda MoAgri and WINBAN eradicated it from Carricou shortly after. Predominantly it attacks the Bluggoe, Moko fig (Macambou in SLU). Control of the disease costs XCD $600,000 (1992 news article) annually to the banana sector.
